freemarker.core

Class TemplateNumberFormat

  • java.lang.Object
    • freemarker.core.TemplateNumberFormat

  • public abstract class TemplateNumberFormat
extends Object
    Represents a number format; used in templates for formatting and parsing with that format. This is similar to Java's NumberFormat, but made to fit the requirements of FreeMarker. Also, it makes easier to define formats that can't be represented with Java's existing NumberFormat implementations.

    Implementations need not be thread-safe if the TemplateNumberFormatFactory doesn't recycle them among different Environment-s. As far as FreeMarker's concerned, instances are bound to a single Environment, and Environment-s are thread-local objects.

    Since:
    2.3.24

      • format

        public abstract String format(TemplateNumberModel numberModel)
                       throws UnformattableNumberException,
                              TemplateModelException
        Parameters:
        numberModel - The date/time/dateTime to format. Most implementations will just work with the return value of TemplateDateModel.getAsDate(), but some may format differently depending on the properties of a custom TemplateDateModel implementation.
        Returns:
        The date/time/dateTime as text, with no escaping (like no HTML escaping). Can't be null.
        Throws:
        UnformattableNumberException - When a TemplateDateModel can't be formatted because of the value/properties of the TemplateDateModel. The most often used subclass is UnknownDateTypeFormattingUnsupportedException.
        TemplateModelException - Exception thrown by the dateModel object when calling its methods.

      • format

        public abstract <MO extends TemplateMarkupOutputModel> MO format(TemplateNumberModel dateModel,
                                                                 MarkupOutputFormat<MO> outputFormat)
                                                          throws UnformattableNumberException,
                                                                 TemplateModelException
        [Not yet used, might changes in 2.3.24 final] Formats the number to markup instead of to plain text, or returns null that will make FreeMarker call format(TemplateNumberModel) and escape its result. If the markup format would be just the result of format(TemplateNumberModel) escaped, it should return null.
        Throws:
        UnformattableNumberException
        TemplateModelException

      • format

        public <MO extends TemplateMarkupOutputModel> boolean format(TemplateNumberModel dateModel,
                                                             MarkupOutputFormat<MO> outputFormat,
                                                             Writer out)
                                                      throws UnformattableNumberException,
                                                             TemplateModelException,
                                                             IOException
        [Not yet used, might changes in 2.3.24 final] Same as format(TemplateNumberModel, MarkupOutputFormat), but prints the result to a Writer instead of returning it. This can be utilized for some optimizatoin. In the case where format(TemplateNumberModel, MarkupOutputFormat) would return null, it returns false. It writes to the Writer exactly if the return value is true.

        The default implementation in TemplateNumberFormat builds on calls format(TemplateNumberModel, MarkupOutputFormat) and writes its result to the Writer.

        Throws:
        UnformattableNumberException
        TemplateModelException
        IOException
